Introduction

Gyeongwon, formely known as Yuha is a South Korean singer-songwriter, rapper and model under Petite Concierge. She is a former member of the girl groups PRISTIN and HINAPIA.

In 2016, Gyeongwon participated in Mnet's survival television show, Produce 101, along with other five trainees from her agency, Pledis Entertainment. She was eliminated in episode 8 after ranking 48th place.

On 2017, Pledis announced Gyeongwon, under the stage name Yuha, as a member of PRISTIN, which debuted on March 21, 2017 with the mini album "Hi!" and its title track, "Wee Woo".
